        <num>CC 890</num>
        <heading>890.  Usufruct of surviving spouse</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 890.  Usufruct of surviving spouse
If the deceased spouse is survived by descendants, the surviving spouse shall have a usufruct over the decedent's share of the community property to the extent that the decedent has not disposed of it by testament.  This usufruct terminates when the surviving spouse dies or remarries, whichever occurs first.</p>
        </content>
